'''Video gaming in Ghana''' has been developing in the country since the early  1980s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=pZb5CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA20&dq=video%20games%20in%20ghana&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi1y-XVhKLRAhVBKcAKHYj_BdMQ6AEILDAC#v=onepage&q=video%20games%20in%20ghana&f=false|title=Video Games Around the World|first1=Mark J. P.|last1=Wolf|first2=Toru|last2=Iwatani|date=1 May 2015|publisher=MIT Press|accessdate=1 January 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=deBFx7QAwsQC&pg=PA19&dq=video%20games%20in%20ghana&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi1y-XVhKLRAhVBKcAKHYj_BdMQ6AEIIzAA#v=onepage&q=video%20games%20in%20ghana&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of Video Games: M-Z|date=1 January 2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|accessdate=1 January 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=nt15DAAAQBAJ&pg=PA374&lpg=PA374&dq=Video%20gaming%20in%20ghana&source=bl&ots=WLeLA9_GG-&sig=PBopUzq9w8nAZlE1aAJkMweIYlo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi59_Ty9qHRAhVFIcAKHftLAIg4KBDoAQg4MAU#v=onepage&q=Video%20gaming%20in%20ghana&f=false|title=Examining the Evolution of Gaming and Its Impact on Social, Cultural, and Political Perspectives|first1=Valentine, Keri|last1=Duncan|first2=Jensen, Lucas|last2=John|date=20 June 2016|publisher=IGI Global|accessdate=1 January 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=N4bDCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT109&lpg=PT109&dq=Video%20gaming%20in%20ghana&source=bl&ots=nx9JyHfp-h&sig=BcHa1WSt-trtNAOlhpAgc_1wU0g&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjwrv7z8KHRAhXKDcAKHeP5Ds44WhDoAQg5MAY#v=onepage&q=Video%20gaming%20in%20ghana&f=false|title=Locating Emerging Media|first1=Germaine R.|last1=Halegoua|first2=Ben|last2=Aslinger|date=17 March 2016|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=1 January 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref> [[Leti Arts]] is one of the emerging [[video game companies]] in Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2013/03/consider-the-work-of-ghanas-leti-games-comics-for-your-next-film-project-136964/|title=Consider The Work Of Ghana’s Leti Games & Comics For Your Next Film Project… - IndieWire|first=Tambay A.|last=Obenson|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>


As of August 2016, the [[Government of Ghana|Government]] doesn't regulate video games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghanabusinessnews.com/2016/08/20/regulation-of-video-games-not-under-our-jurisdiction-commission/|title=Regulation of video games not under our jurisdiction - Commission|date=20 August 2016|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>



Various organizations such as Gamer TV, Madagastar Esports,AnTrix Gaming,GameNerd,Giiks Gaming City and GasBros Gaming Network are some pioneers in the industry. Video Gaming  and Gamers have been  the rise for the last decade. Primarily Tournaments are used to bring gamers around to associate and expand the gaming space.Events like the Annual [[Global Game Jam]]  have greatly helped in the establishment of Gaming as a career choice.Organisations like Virtual Union and Gamers Republic are pushing for pro gamers and Associations like the Ghana E-sports Association are pushing to usher in a new era for E-sports in Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news24.com/MyNews24/ghana-enters-the-international-esports-arena-20160127|title=Ghana enters the international  eSports arena|publisher=|accessdate=10 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/We-need-support-to-participate-in-international-tournaments-Esports-Ghana-635306|title=We need support to participate in international tournaments – Esports Ghana|website=www.ghanaweb.com|accessdate=10 November 2018}}</ref> Tournaments are also held in major cities like Accra and Kumasi. Video Gaming and eSports in general is slowly been accepted and integrated into the Ghanaian culture. 

